FOOD POISONING, FACTORY WORKERS - INDONESIA (BATAM)
***************************************************
ProMED-mail post
<http://www.promedmail.org>
ProMED-mail is a program of the
International Society for Infectious Diseases
<http://www.isid.org>
Date: Fri, 17 Sep 2004
From: Alfonso Rodriguez <ajrm_msds@yahoo.es>
Source: The Jakarta Post, Indonesia [edited]
<http://www.thejakartapost.com/detailnational.asp?fileid=20040917.D05&irec=4>

Over 100 get suspected food poisoning in Batam
---------------------------------------------------
Over 100 employees of a contact lens factory in Batam were admitted
to hospitals on Thu, 16 Sep 2004, allegedly for food poisoning.
Deputy director of Batam Authority Hospital Afdalun A. Hakim
confirmed the hospital was treating 55 employees, most of whom were
dehydrated after vomiting uncontrollably. Other patients were
treated at Casa Medical Center and Batam Industrial Park Medical
Center.
Meanwhile, a 25-year-old, who spoke on behalf of the employees at
Casa Medical Center, recalled that over 100 employees were
hospitalized after eating breakfast provided to them by the
management of contact lens maker PT Ciba Vision. According to her
records, some 50 employees were treated at Casa Medical Center, 30 at
Batam Industrial Park Medical Center and the remaining 55 at Batam
Authority Hospital.
Separately, head of Batam Municipality Health Office Puardi Djarius
said the office was investigating the case. "We will check whether
the food was hygienically prepared," said Puardi.
--
ProMED-mail
<promed@promedmail.org>
[The incubation period is not stated, nor is the length of illness or
the suspected vehicle of the presumptive food poisoning.
Staphylococcal enterotoxin disease, which has an incubation period of
4-8 hours, is associated with prominent vomiting, minimal diarrhea,
and little if any fever. The illness' length is generally 24 hours
or less. - Mod.LL]
